<span id="freeTextContainer4992974242333497248">Literary reportage, which paints and details the history, stories, lives, deaths and mechanisms of the world trafficking of cocaine, from Escobar&apos;s Colombia to the Mexico of the Zetas, passing through West Africa and the Calabrian Aspromonte to Holland, Germany, Australia, by sea, by feet, train, sky, submarine, pigeons, stomaches..<br/><br/>Incredible and frightening numbers and stories, told with insight and passion. I have found the writing a little too &quot;poetic&quot; for my tastes every now and then, as wel</span>
  <span id="freeText4992974242333497248" style="display:none">Literary reportage, which paints and details the history, stories, lives, deaths and mechanisms of the world trafficking of cocaine, from Escobar's Colombia to the Mexico of the Zetas, passing through West Africa and the Calabrian Aspromonte to Holland, Germany, Australia, by sea, by feet, train, sky, submarine, pigeons, stomaches..<br /><br />Incredible and frightening numbers and stories, told with insight and passion. I have found the writing a little too "poetic" for my tastes every now and then, as well as the choice to list long lists of facts, numbers, names, but this does not detract from the value of the book itself.</span>
