<div id="review_1343383871" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/1343383871" />
    <a title="Jason Gonsalez" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/11250899-jason-gonsalez"><img alt="Jason Gonsalez" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1447342598p2/11250899.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/1343383871?book_show_action=true">Jul 23, 2015</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Jason Gonsalez" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Jason Gonsalez" href="/user/show/11250899-jason-gonsalez">Jason Gonsalez</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="really liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">really liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>



        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer1343383871" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer13614133899798339358">At first I was wondering what did I get myself in to. But man with this Novel you realize that cocaine doesn&apos;t just hurt the person using it, it effects a lot more people than what you think. The brutal stories this writer speaks of are heart wrenching. No good news comes out of something involving the Drug Lords. Good for them for a bit but, in the end cocaine will find a way to even screw them and take them for all they&apos;ve got too. If you ever wanted to know about cocaine and the people who gr</span>
  <span id="freeText13614133899798339358" style="display:none">At first I was wondering what did I get myself in to. But man with this Novel you realize that cocaine doesn't just hurt the person using it, it effects a lot more people than what you think. The brutal stories this writer speaks of are heart wrenching. No good news comes out of something involving the Drug Lords. Good for them for a bit but, in the end cocaine will find a way to even screw them and take them for all they've got too. If you ever wanted to know about cocaine and the people who grow it and sell it, Robert Saviano is your Willy Wonka he has your golden ticket in this Novel.</span>
  <a data-text-id="13614133899798339358" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
